column5: we've found lots of unique items in outpost camps and can usually figure out what they are used for - but we found these at the North Caribou Lake cabin and are at a loss to explain. photo attached. any thoughts?? phish
dammn wally - I think you got it! thanks, phish
I use those all the time to make home-made Egg McMuffins!
I use them for pancakes. Perfectly round and then the batter does not go all over the place. Pour the batter let them cook until air bubbles come out of the top, and them remove the ring and flip!
You sure they aren't tip ups?
Never even heard of such a thing.
